What we are really interested in is the availability of that carbon. Carbon recalcitrance, or residence, in the soil, is what we are most interested in. Labile, easily decomposed carbon, while temporarily adding to the soil carbon stock, will not remain long in the soil and will not likely contribute to the resting carbon stock.\
